QuantumLeap E-Commerce Test Automation

A complete end-to-end automation framework built to validate both web and API layers of a modern e-commerce system using SauceDemo and ReqRes applications.  
This project demonstrates a full SDET workflow, including Selenium + TestNG, Cucumber BDD, REST Assured, and Extent Reports integration.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Project Overview

The QuantumLeap Framework automates
1. UI Functional Testing – Login, Add to Cart, and End-to-End Purchase flow on [SauceDemo](httpswww.saucedemo.com).
2. API Testing – CRUD operations validation using [ReqRes API](httpsreqres.in).
3. BDD Integration – Add Item to Cart scenario written in Gherkin syntax.
4. Reporting – HTML reports with screenshots for failed UI tests using Extent Reports.
5. Non-Functional Testing Concepts – Performance and Security testing documentation.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Tech Stack

 Category  Tools  Frameworks 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Language  Java 
 Build Tool  Maven 
 UI Automation  Selenium WebDriver 
 Test Framework  TestNG 
 BDD Framework  Cucumber 
 API Testing  REST Assured 
 Reporting  Extent Reports 
 Design Pattern  Page Object Model (POM) 
 Version Control  Git  GitHub 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Key Features
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 - UI Tests (SauceDemo):
- Data-driven Login test using TestNG `@DataProvider`
- End-to-End Purchase Flow:
  - Login → Add Item → Verify Cart → Checkout → Confirm Order
- POM architecture for maintainability
- Explicit waits, screenshot capture, and JS Executor usage

 - BDD (Cucumber + TestNG):
- Add-to-cart scenario written in Gherkin format
- Step Definitions reuse POM page methods
- TestRunner integrated with TestNG XML

 - API Tests (ReqRes):
- **GET** → Fetch user list  
- **POST** → Create new user  
- **PUT** → Update existing user  
- Validations for status codes and response bodies

 - Reports:
- Extent Report auto-generated after every run
- Screenshots for any failed UI test steps
Non-Functional Docs:**
- Performance Testing Plan for Login functionality
- Security Scenarios (Authentication Bypass & XSS)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Run the Tests

Pre-requisites
- Java JDK 11+
- Maven 3+
- TestNG Plugin (optional for IDE)
- Chrome Browser & ChromeDriver (auto-managed via WebDriverManager)

Steps to Run
bash
Clone this repo
git clone https://github.com/AyanKumarDash01/QuantumLeap.git
cd QuantumLeap-Automation

Run all tests
mvn clean test

Or run specific TestNG suite

mvn test -DsuiteXmlFile=testng.xml
